// Pipeline with LSP analysis - demonstrates automatic code quality checks
// Every write_file triggers async LSP analysis
digraph LSPExample {
    graph [
        goal="Create a factorial calculator with automatic quality checks"
    ]

    start [shape=Mdiamond, label="Start"]
    exit  [shape=Msquare, label="Exit"]

    // The agent creates the code - LSP analysis runs automatically after write_file
    implement [
        label="Implement Factorial",
        prompt="Create a file called factorial.go with a Factorial(n int) function that calculates factorial.

The function should:
1. Handle n >= 0
2. Return an error for negative numbers  
3. Use iteration (not recursion) for performance
4. Include basic error handling

After writing the file, the system will automatically analyze it with LSP to check for issues.

Write the file using write_file, then check the logs for any LSP diagnostics."
    ]

    // The agent can explicitly call lsp_analyze if needed
    verify [
        label="Verify Code Quality",
        prompt="Use the lsp_analyze tool to check factorial.go for any issues.

The lsp_analyze tool will:
- Parse the Go code
- Check for syntax errors
- Find potential issues
- Return diagnostic messages

If issues are found, fix them. If no issues, proceed."
    ]

    start -> implement -> verify -> exit
}
